cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on word vector representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for constructing these vectors, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of linguistic resources like WordNet and FrameNet, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's focus on word vectors and their evaluation could also make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
